The paper deals with graph partitioning and distance-related problems, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and game theory (cs.GT). The focus on diameter and padding parameters suggests a strong connection to data structures and computational geometry, while the mention of doubling dimension and cover schemes points towards numerical analysis and discrete mathematics.
